<subSubSection id="C32B6553FF8F3A7ABBD2FA77657CBAEE" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8E36D8FF8F3A7ABBD2FA77657CBAEE" blockId="1.[151,1437,1452,2017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8F3A7ABBD2FA776152BAC3" bold="true" box="[151,266,1452,1477]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. F 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABA77FA776164BAC2" box="[306,316,1452,1476]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
with basiventral denticle, with adjacent basal spines stronger (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8F3A7ABF71FA776427BAC2" box="[1076,1151,1452,1477]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABF2AFA776427BAC2" box="[1135,1151,1452,1476]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
); epandrium fused with hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8F3A7ABA68FA14612ABAEE" box="[301,370,1487,1512]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABA27FA0B612ABAEE" box="[354,370,1488,1512]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
); surstylus complex, subovate lobe with spine-like setae at tip on inner face (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8F3A7ABF94FA14654EBAEE" box="[1233,1302,1487,1512]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABE43FA14654EBAEE" box="[1286,1302,1487,1512]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32B6553FF8F3A78BB82FA2F6155BDB7" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="212" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8E36D8FF8F3A7ABB82FA2F65C0B8E7" blockId="1.[151,1437,1452,2017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8F3A7ABB82FA2F61C4B90B" bold="true" box="[199,412,1524,1549]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8F3A7ABAEFFA2F61B3B90A" box="[426,491,1524,1549]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABA9BFA2F61B3B90A" box="[478,491,1524,1548]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8F3A7AB946FA2F621BB90B" bold="true" box="[515,579,1524,1549]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">Head</emphasis>
. Dark brown to black, antenna and mouthparts yellow with all setae whitish; ocellar triangle with 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABAD7F9C361F8B936" box="[402,416,1560,1584]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
pair of proclinate setae; anterior ocellus larger. Eyes iridescent black, very narrowly separated on face bearing fine reclinate setulae. Frons with 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7AB86FF9E76360B952" box="[810,824,1596,1620]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="3.0">3</number>
setulae; small vertical setae contiguous with uniseriate postocular setae. Occiput bearing scattered fine hairs. Clypeus with rather dense short downwardly directed pile. Proboscis slightly curved, with setae yellow. Antenna with scape and pedicel bearing distinct short dorsal setulae; postpedicel about 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABA23F97C61D0B9C6" box="[358,392,1703,1728]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X as long as wide, stylus ~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7AB982F97362B2B9C6" box="[711,746,1704,1728]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="0.8">0.8</number>
X as long as postpedicel. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8F3A7ABF4AF97C6430B9C6" bold="true" box="[1039,1128,1703,1728]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8F3A7ABF3DF97C64E3B9C6" box="[1144,1211,1703,1728]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABFEBF97364E3B9C6" box="[1198,1211,1704,1728]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Elongate, slightly arched ventrally, dorsum yellow except brownish on prothoracic collar, narrowly behind postpronotal lobe, suture between katepisternum and meron; antepronotum with anterior margin almost straight; scutum with yellow setae, very small and fine except one notopleural. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8F3A7AB9C7F8CF62E2B82B" bold="true" box="[642,698,1812,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8F3A7AB98CF8CF6352B82A" box="[713,778,1812,1837]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7AB9B8F8CF6352B82A" box="[765,778,1812,1836]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Whitish yellow. C 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7AB8B4F8CF63A3B82A" box="[1009,1019,1812,1836]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABF5DF8CF6462B82A" box="[1048,1082,1812,1836]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.4">1.4</number>
X longer than distance between C 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABBE8F8E360EFB856" box="[173,183,1848,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
and C2, 
<date id="FF8F1018FF8F3A7ABA67F8EC611CB856" box="[290,324,1847,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">6X</date>
as long as wide with some pale dorsoapical setae. F 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7AB8E7F8E363F4B856" box="[930,940,1848,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7AB88BF8E363B7B856" box="[974,1007,1848,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.1">1.1</number>
X as long as C 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABFE5F8E364F3B856" box="[1184,1195,1848,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
, 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABFFCF8EC6483B856" box="[1209,1243,1847,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="3.5">3.5</number>
–4.0X as long as wide; femoral formula 
<date id="FF8F1018FF8F3A7ABADAF88761BFB873" box="[415,487,1884,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1923-07-01">
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABADAF88761F5B873" box="[415,429,1884,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="7.0">7</number>
/ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABAF3F887618BB873" box="[438,467,1884,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="23.0">23</number>
/ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABA9BF88761BFB873" box="[478,487,1884,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
</date>
+ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABAB2F887624BB873" box="[503,531,1884,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="21.0">21</number>
/ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7AB958F8876272B873" box="[541,554,1884,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="5.0">5</number>
, basal spines stronger (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8F3A7AB870F8876323B872" box="[821,891,1884,1909]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="210">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7AB82EF8876323B872" box="[875,891,1884,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
); denticles confined to distal 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABF8BF88764ABB872" box="[1230,1267,1884,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="0.7">0.7</number>
, 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABE45F8876556B872" box="[1280,1294,1884,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="2.0">2</number>
rows linear, black, without distal discontinuity, converging distally but divergent at tip. T 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7AB8B6F85B63A5B89E" box="[1011,1021,1920,1944]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABF5FF85B6465B89E" box="[1050,1085,1920,1944]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="0.8">0.8</number>
X as long as F 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABFA4F85B64B4B89E" box="[1249,1260,1920,1944]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
, evenly curved, ventral face shallowly concave; with 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7AB907F87F6208B8BA" box="[578,592,1956,1980]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="2.0">2</number>
rows of 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7AB9FCF87F62A6B8BA" box="[697,766,1956,1980]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="19.0" valueMax="21.0" valueMin="17.0">17–21</number>
sharply pointed spinose setae ventrally; dorsal ciliation of decumbent short pale setulae, denser distally; with small apicoventral extension on T 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8F3A7ABF17F8136404B8E6" box="[1106,1116,1992,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="210" value="1.0">1</number>
bearing strong apical spine.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF4E6650FF8C3A79BBD2F85A64F6B8D2" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="211" targetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8B8E36D8FF8C3A79BBD2F85A64F6B8D2" blockId="2.[151,1436,1921,2004]" pageId="2" pageNumber="211">
