<paragraph id="8B8E36D8FF8D3A78BBD2FF4C6155BDB7" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1013]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Mid and hind legs slender with fine setae but T 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B981FF436289BFB6" box="[708,721,152,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="3.0">3</number>
with ‘comb’ of short setae posteroapically. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8D3A78BF94FF4C654ABFB6" bold="true" box="[1233,1298,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Wing</emphasis>
. Membrane faintly yellow, veins brownish; R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B950FF106245BFDF" box="[533,541,203,217]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B963FF106275BFDF" box="[550,557,203,217]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="3.0">3</number>
long and straight, not strongly curved towards C apically, joining C ~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BE20FF6765D0BFD2" box="[1381,1416,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="0.8">0.8</number>
X distance between end of R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BA87FF2A6192BFF9" box="[450,458,241,255]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
and R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B951FF2A6244BFF9" box="[532,540,241,255]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="4.0">4</number>
; R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B97BFF2A621EBFF9" box="[574,582,241,255]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B90AFF2A620EBFF9" box="[591,598,241,255]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="5.0">5</number>
fork angle acute (~ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B878FF396305BFFD" box="[829,861,226,251]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="60.0">60</number>
°), distal to position of M 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BF3DFF2A6425BFF9" box="[1144,1149,241,255]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BFC2FF2A64C8BFF9" box="[1159,1168,241,255]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="2.0">2</number>
fork by ~ 
<date id="FF8F1018FF8D3A78BE44FF38657BBFFD" box="[1281,1315,227,251]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BE44FF386557BFFD" box="[1281,1295,227,251]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
as long as R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BBECFEC360E9BE20" box="[169,177,280,294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="4.0">4</number>
; R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BB91FEC36084BE20" box="[212,220,280,294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BA68FEC3616DBE20" box="[301,309,280,294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
convergent distally; vein R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B92AFEC3622FBE20" box="[623,631,280,294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="5.0">5</number>
~ 
<date id="FF8F1018FF8D3A78B9D2FED162E1BE24" box="[663,697,266,290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B9D2FED162FCBE24" box="[663,676,266,290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
as long as R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B808FEC3630DBE20" box="[845,853,280,294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="4.0">4</number>
; cell bm+dm short, ending at level of R 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BE5AFEC3657FBE20" box="[1311,1319,280,294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="1.0">1</number>
, ~2.0X as long as cell br. Halter whitish yellow. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8D3A78B909FEEB6298BE4F" bold="true" box="[588,704,304,329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78B997FEEB6362BE4F" box="[722,826,304,329]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
). Tergites 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B8F6FEEB6385BE4F" box="[947,989,304,329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="3.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="1.0">1–6</number>
and 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BF52FEEA647DBE4F" box="[1047,1061,305,329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="8.0">8</number>
brownish; tergite 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BFB2FEEA655DBE4E" box="[1271,1285,305,328]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="7.0">7</number>
and sternites yellowish. Tergites with distinct setae on posterior margin; tergite 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B8D7FE8E63F8BE6B" box="[914,928,341,365]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="8.0">8</number>
slightly shorter than sternite 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BFB6FE8E655BBE6B" box="[1267,1283,341,365]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="8.0">8</number>
. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8D3A78BE57FE8F65CDBE6B" bold="true" box="[1298,1429,340,365]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Brown. Cercus with subbasal pointed projection, rounded at apex and distinctly setose on outer face (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78BE4DFEA3650ABE97" box="[1288,1362,376,401]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Figs 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BE04FEA2650ABE97" box="[1345,1362,377,401]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
); right and left cerci close together dorsally (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78B979FE4762D8BEB3" box="[572,640,412,437]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B935FE4762D8BEB3" box="[624,640,412,437]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). Epandrium wide, subtriangular (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78BF45FE47641DBEB3" box="[1024,1093,412,437]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BF70FE46641DBEB3" box="[1077,1093,413,437]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
), scattered setae on outer face, fused with hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78BAF7FE1B61A1BEDF" box="[434,505,448,473]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BAACFE1A61A1BEDF" box="[489,505,449,473]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Surstylus present, complex, subovate lobe, with spine-like setae at tip on inner face (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78BB91FE3F610DBEFB" box="[212,341,484,509]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Figs 4, 6, 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BA00FE3E610DBEFB" box="[325,341,485,509]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium rather subtriangular (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78B9AEFE3F6377BEFB" box="[747,815,484,509]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B865FE3E6377BEFB" box="[800,815,485,509]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
), without distinct setae; gonocoxal apodeme projecting as narrow process just beyond anterior margin of hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78B8EEFDD363A2BD27" box="[939,1018,520,545]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78B8ACFDD263A2BD27" box="[1001,1018,521,545]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subepandrial sclerite wide, with subquadrate anterior projection and two subtriangular posterior processes (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78B8BAFDF7641FBD43" box="[1023,1095,556,581]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BF72FDF7641FBD43" box="[1079,1095,556,581]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Phallus (
<figureCitation id="130A2A5DFF8D3A78BF82FDF76557BD43" box="[1223,1295,556,581]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,193,1900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Hemerodromia amazonensis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 1. habitus, lateral view; 2. fore femur and tibia; 3. abdomen from segment 4 to terminalia; 4. terminalia, lateral view; 5. cercus, dorsal view; 6. subepandrial sclerite, surstylus and epandrium, dorsal view; 7. phallus, lateral view; 8. hypandrium, epandrium and surstylus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252069/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">
Fig. 
<number id="3DF924FFFF8D3A78BE45FDF66557BD43" box="[1280,1295,557,581]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) sclerotized basally, extending just beyond hypandrium, with pointed dorsal projection apically and apical short membranous area with scattered spicules. Ejaculatory apodeme absent. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8D3A78B86BFDAF6398BD8B" bold="true" box="[814,960,628,653]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Body length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity id="4CC99B3DFF8D3A78B894FDAF6473BD8A" box="[977,1067,628,653]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
; 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8D3A78BF7CFDAF649EBD8B" bold="true" box="[1081,1222,628,653]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">wing length</emphasis>
: 
<quantity id="4CC99B3DFF8D3A78BF93FDAE6569BD8A" box="[1238,1329,629,653]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="3" pageNumber="212" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B945EACAFF8D3A78BE7BFDAF65CDBD8B" bold="true" box="[1342,1429,628,653]" pageId="3" pageNumber="212">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
